521
00:40:01,460 --> 00:40:05,620
Now that's a correct
and useful formula.

522
00:40:05,620 --> 00:40:07,220
Are there others?

523
00:40:07,220 --> 00:40:08,740
Many.

524
00:40:08,740 --> 00:40:10,620
For example?

525
00:40:10,620 --> 00:40:15,500
Along with angels and guardian
angels, there are powers:

526
00:40:15,500 --> 00:40:17,500
Archangels,

527
00:40:17,500 --> 00:40:20,340
seraphim, cherubim.

528
00:40:20,340 --> 00:40:24,060
Intermediary beings
par excellence.

529
00:40:24,060 --> 00:40:25,780
Intermediary
between consciousness

530
00:40:25,780 --> 00:40:28,580
and unconsciousness?

531
00:40:28,580 --> 00:40:29,980
Well, of course.

532
00:40:31,420 --> 00:40:33,980
But also between
nature and man,

533
00:40:33,980 --> 00:40:36,780
man and the divine,

534
00:40:36,780 --> 00:40:40,700
reason and Eros.

535
00:40:40,700 --> 00:40:43,220
Feminine and masculine,

536
00:40:43,220 --> 00:40:45,300
darkness and light,

537
00:40:45,300 --> 00:40:47,100
matter and spirit.

538
00:40:47,100 --> 00:40:48,580
[SIGHS]

539
00:40:50,140 --> 00:40:52,900
So it's come back
to my old passion again:

540
00:40:54,300 --> 00:40:57,500
philosophy of religion.

541
00:40:57,500 --> 00:41:00,020
Yes,

542
00:41:00,020 --> 00:41:02,340
for you it will always
come back to that.

543
00:41:04,860 --> 00:41:07,260
But I can't believe
in the objective reality

544
00:41:07,260 --> 00:41:10,060
of the person
with whom I'm conversing. I--

545
00:41:11,420 --> 00:41:15,060
I can only think of him
as my double.

546
00:41:15,060 --> 00:41:17,660
Well, in a sense,

547
00:41:17,660 --> 00:41:19,820
that's what he is, but...

548
00:41:21,500 --> 00:41:25,180
that doesn't mean
he doesn't exist

549
00:41:25,180 --> 00:41:27,780
in an objective way
independently.

550
00:41:27,780 --> 00:41:29,740
Oh, I'd like to be convinced,
but--

551
00:41:29,740 --> 00:41:34,460
In metaphysical controversies,
empirical proofs

552
00:41:34,460 --> 00:41:36,900
lose their value, but...

553
00:41:41,340 --> 00:41:44,460
wouldn't you enjoy receiving

554
00:41:44,460 --> 00:41:47,500
a few fresh roses

555
00:41:47,500 --> 00:41:49,220
picked from the garden?

556
00:41:49,220 --> 00:41:51,420
I've always liked roses.

557
00:41:51,420 --> 00:41:53,660
Well, where would you like me
to put them?

558
00:41:55,580 --> 00:41:58,460
Not in the vase,
at any rate.

559
00:42:00,780 --> 00:42:03,740
One right here

560
00:42:03,740 --> 00:42:05,220
in my hand...

561
00:42:07,380 --> 00:42:10,740
as I'm holding it now, open.

562
00:42:10,740 --> 00:42:12,420
[#]

563
00:42:19,900 --> 00:42:21,900
And another on my knee?

564
00:42:28,220 --> 00:42:30,060
The third rose.

565
00:42:30,060 --> 00:42:32,660
Where do you want me
to put the third rose?

566
00:42:34,140 --> 00:42:35,860
Let's see.

567
00:42:39,100 --> 00:42:42,220
Things are more serious
than we thought.

568
00:42:42,220 --> 00:42:46,540
We know now why the Gestapo
will try anything,

569
00:42:46,540 --> 00:42:48,820
anything, in order to get
their hands on you.

570
00:42:50,820 --> 00:42:51,940
Why?

571
00:42:51,940 --> 00:42:55,220
Among the intimates
of Goebbels,

572
00:42:55,220 --> 00:42:58,140
there is an enigmatic
and ambiguous person,

573
00:42:58,140 --> 00:43:01,020
a certain Dr. Josef Rudolf.

574
00:43:01,020 --> 00:43:03,500
[CAMERA CLICKS]

575
00:43:03,500 --> 00:43:05,100
[SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

576
00:43:05,100 --> 00:43:08,540
<i>Dr. Rudolf believes that
electrocution by a current</i>

577
00:43:08,540 --> 00:43:10,460
<i>of at least a million volts</i>

578
00:43:10,460 --> 00:43:12,700
<i>could produce
a radical mutation</i>

579
00:43:12,700 --> 00:43:14,620
<i>of the human species.</i>

580
00:43:17,620 --> 00:43:18,940
<i>Word of these experiments</i>

581
00:43:18,940 --> 00:43:21,820
<i>has reached the ear
of Adolf Hitler,</i>

582
00:43:21,820 --> 00:43:25,340
<i>who has become personally
interested in your case.</i>

583
00:43:25,340 --> 00:43:27,260
[MEN SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

584
00:43:27,260 --> 00:43:30,620
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

585
00:43:30,620 --> 00:43:33,300
[IN GERMAN] Attention!
The experiment begins!

586
00:43:35,340 --> 00:43:37,180
[MEN SHOUTING]

587
00:43:55,580 --> 00:43:59,900
[IN ENGLISH] They want
us to lend you to them

588
00:43:59,900 --> 00:44:02,340
for a period of time.

589
00:44:02,340 --> 00:44:04,700
God help me.

590
00:44:04,700 --> 00:44:05,580
Time, Dominic,

591
00:44:07,100 --> 00:44:10,020
we are running out of time.

592
00:44:10,020 --> 00:44:12,380
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

593
00:44:12,380 --> 00:44:14,180
[MAN SPEAKING IN GERMAN
OVER PA]

594
00:44:19,700 --> 00:44:22,260
MAN [IN GERMAN]: Austrian-Swiss
border. Passport control.

595
00:44:22,260 --> 00:44:26,060
Please disembark
with all luggage.

596
00:44:33,660 --> 00:44:37,260
[MAN SPEAKING IN GERMAN
OVER PA]

597
00:44:39,820 --> 00:44:40,860
[SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

598
00:44:40,860 --> 00:44:41,700
[SPEAKS IN GERMAN]

599
00:44:50,140 --> 00:44:51,900
[TRAIN CHUGGING]
[BELL DINGING]

600
00:44:57,180 --> 00:45:01,460
[MAN SPEAKING IN GERMAN
OVER PA]

601
00:45:08,180 --> 00:45:10,820
An order has just come in
from Vienna

602
00:45:10,820 --> 00:45:15,140
that certain nationals
will be detained.

603
00:45:15,140 --> 00:45:18,420
But why? I have
a valid passport and visa.

604
00:45:18,420 --> 00:45:19,820
Please take a step back.

605
00:45:25,980 --> 00:45:27,500
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

606
00:45:31,220 --> 00:45:33,060
[CHATTERING IN GERMAN]

607
00:45:45,700 --> 00:45:47,820
Go on!

608
00:45:47,820 --> 00:45:51,580
My cooperation with the Nazis
is only symbolic.

609
00:45:51,580 --> 00:45:52,220
Go ahead.

610
00:45:54,420 --> 00:45:55,580
DOMINIC:
Thank you.

611
00:45:55,580 --> 00:45:57,180
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

612
00:45:57,180 --> 00:45:58,900
[#]

613
00:46:27,580 --> 00:46:28,740
<i>DOMINIC [IN ENGLISH]:
Geneva.</i>

614
00:46:28,740 --> 00:46:31,900
<i>1941, May the 7th.</i>

615
00:46:31,900 --> 00:46:34,620
<i>Dominic Matei, dictation.</i>

616
00:46:41,580 --> 00:46:44,300
The documents in the Geneva
safety-deposit box

617
00:46:44,300 --> 00:46:47,460
summarize my life,
which was profoundly changed

618
00:46:47,460 --> 00:46:49,460
in the spring of 1938,

619
00:46:49,460 --> 00:46:51,620
in front of the Gara de Nord
railway station

620
00:46:51,620 --> 00:46:52,900
in Bucharest.

621
00:46:52,900 --> 00:46:54,340
My first experiences

622
00:46:54,340 --> 00:46:58,100
were described and analyzed
by Professor Roman Stanciulescu,

623
00:46:58,100 --> 00:47:01,740
in reports which were
confiscated by the Nazis.

624
00:47:01,740 --> 00:47:04,540
[WHIRRING]

625
00:47:04,540 --> 00:47:06,460
<i>[#]</i>

626
00:47:06,460 --> 00:47:08,860
<i>DOMINIC:
The war rages around me.</i>

627
00:47:08,860 --> 00:47:11,580
<i>I am a fugitive
in neutral Switzerland,</i>

628
00:47:11,580 --> 00:47:12,980
<i>encircled by the Axis powers.</i>

629
00:47:18,660 --> 00:47:21,900
<i>My Romanian homeland has
made a pact with the devil,</i>

630
00:47:21,900 --> 00:47:23,660
<i>Adolf Hitler,</i>

631
00:47:23,660 --> 00:47:26,020
<i>and may soon be under siege.</i>

632
00:47:27,340 --> 00:47:29,740
<i>[GUNSHOT]</i>

633
00:47:29,740 --> 00:47:31,580
<i>I've lost contact
with my dear friend,</i>

634
00:47:31,580 --> 00:47:33,180
<i>Professor Stanciulescu,</i>

635
00:47:33,180 --> 00:47:34,340
<i>which could mean
that he's been killed.</i>

636
00:47:37,580 --> 00:47:39,300
[CAMERA CLICKING]

637
00:47:44,100 --> 00:47:45,540
<i>I live in fear,</i>

638
00:47:45,540 --> 00:47:47,980
<i>dreading what awaits
in the alleyways.</i>

639
00:47:47,980 --> 00:47:50,140
<i>Eluding capture by my wits,</i>

640
00:47:50,140 --> 00:47:52,540
<i>moving from hotel
to rooming house,</i>

641
00:47:52,540 --> 00:47:54,420
<i>always working on my book.</i>

642
00:47:55,460 --> 00:47:57,060
<i>[GUNSHOT]</i>

643
00:47:57,060 --> 00:47:59,500
<i>November the 30th, 1941.</i>

644
00:47:59,500 --> 00:48:04,060
<i>Zurich. Dominic Matei.</i>

645
00:48:04,060 --> 00:48:05,540
<i>I have explained
in portfolio B</i>

646
00:48:05,540 --> 00:48:07,420
<i>how I instinctually
found the talent</i>

647
00:48:07,420 --> 00:48:10,020
<i>to preserve myself.</i>

648
00:48:10,020 --> 00:48:11,900
<i>Living like a secret agent,</i>

649
00:48:11,900 --> 00:48:15,220
<i>I discovered abilities
to forge documents,</i>

650
00:48:15,220 --> 00:48:17,900
<i>change addresses
and prepare disguises.</i>

651
00:48:17,900 --> 00:48:19,060
<i>[GUNSHOT]</i>

652
00:48:24,260 --> 00:48:27,580
<i>Shortly before he disappeared,
Professor Stanciulescu</i>

653
00:48:27,580 --> 00:48:30,220
<i>arranged a bank account
for me in Geneva</i>

654
00:48:30,220 --> 00:48:32,060
<i>under the name
of William Pedersen.</i>

655
00:48:33,740 --> 00:48:36,180
<i>Now, without him,
these funds will be depleted.</i>

656
00:48:36,180 --> 00:48:38,340
Oh, good morning,
Mr. Pedersen.

657
00:48:38,340 --> 00:48:40,940
<i>And I will have
to find other means.</i>

658
00:48:40,940 --> 00:48:41,860
<i>[GUNSHOT]</i>

659
00:48:43,260 --> 00:48:46,540
<i>February the 20th, 1942.</i>

660
00:48:46,540 --> 00:48:48,300
<i>Bern.</i>

661
00:48:48,300 --> 00:48:52,060
<i>I must face the undeniable
and chilling truth,</i>

662
00:48:52,060 --> 00:48:53,540
<i>that I am a mutant.</i>

663
00:48:53,540 --> 00:48:56,860
<i>Like a character
in a science-fiction novel,</i>

664
00:48:56,860 --> 00:49:00,020
<i>I am a strange superman
of the future.</i>

665
00:49:01,660 --> 00:49:06,340
<i>I have access to knowledge
unavailable to mankind.</i>

666
00:49:06,340 --> 00:49:09,180
<i>Powers I don't fully
understand.</i>

667
00:49:11,460 --> 00:49:13,980
<i>[GUNSHOT]</i>

668
00:49:13,980 --> 00:49:18,060
<i>Despite this, I try to behave
as an ordinary intellectual,</i>

669
00:49:18,060 --> 00:49:20,180
<i>working to complete my book,</i>

670
00:49:20,180 --> 00:49:22,300
<i>documenting the origin
of language</i>

671
00:49:22,300 --> 00:49:24,380
<i>and human consciousness.</i>

672
00:49:24,380 --> 00:49:28,220
<i>I began to realize that
with any text I had before me,</i>

673
00:49:28,220 --> 00:49:30,300
<i>if I wanted to know
the content,</i>

674
00:49:30,300 --> 00:49:33,660
<i>I simply...knew it.</i>

675
00:49:35,940 --> 00:49:38,340
<i>[GUNSHOT]</i>

676
00:49:38,340 --> 00:49:41,900
<i>Lake Campione.
October the 23rd, 1942.</i>

677
00:49:45,740 --> 00:49:48,940
<i>I found I could augment
my income.</i>

678
00:49:48,940 --> 00:49:52,340
<i>Winning just enough
not to arouse suspicion.</i>

679
00:49:52,340 --> 00:49:54,900
No more bets.

680
00:49:54,900 --> 00:49:58,300
<i>Nothing is as it seems,
I am the proof of that.</i>

681
00:49:58,300 --> 00:49:59,780
We've got a winner.

682
00:49:59,780 --> 00:50:01,260
MAN:
Dominic Matei?

683
00:50:01,260 --> 00:50:03,540
Dominic Matei.

684
00:50:03,540 --> 00:50:05,860
<i>I trust no one.</i>

685
00:50:07,260 --> 00:50:08,780
Look at these.

686
00:50:08,780 --> 00:50:10,940
See? These were taken
at the clinic

687
00:50:10,940 --> 00:50:13,700
of Dr. Stanciulescu...

688
00:50:13,700 --> 00:50:16,860
in 1938.

689
00:50:16,860 --> 00:50:20,780
And to think, 10 months ago,
on January 8th,

690
00:50:20,780 --> 00:50:22,100
you turned 74 years old.

691
00:50:24,140 --> 00:50:25,180
CROUPIER:
Eleven again.

692
00:50:25,180 --> 00:50:26,540
You're trying
to look older too.

693
00:50:26,540 --> 00:50:28,420
Those glasses aren't
even prescription.

694
00:50:31,460 --> 00:50:34,700
I still don't-- Thank you.
I still don't know

695
00:50:34,700 --> 00:50:36,540
with whom I have the pleasure
to be speaking.

696
00:50:36,540 --> 00:50:38,580
Ted Jones, Jr.

697
00:50:38,580 --> 00:50:41,500
<i>I'm a correspondent
for LIFE magazine.</i>

698
00:50:41,500 --> 00:50:43,660
Listen.

699
00:50:43,660 --> 00:50:46,580
Switzerland is entirely
surrounded by the Axis powers.

700
00:50:46,580 --> 00:50:49,500
I'm cashing out.
Thank you.

701
00:50:49,500 --> 00:50:51,860
I'm on special assignment
for the United States.

702
00:50:51,860 --> 00:50:54,740
I really think you're
confusing me with someone else.

703
00:50:54,740 --> 00:50:57,340
We can protect your identity,
completely.

704
00:50:57,340 --> 00:51:00,060
I have a very powerful
organization behind me.

705
00:51:00,060 --> 00:51:03,100
I know I can be
of some service to you.

706
00:51:03,100 --> 00:51:05,180
We can pay you, or we can make

707
00:51:05,180 --> 00:51:07,340
some arrangements for you,
anything that might help you.

708
00:51:14,780 --> 00:51:16,300
You know,
your English is perfect,

709
00:51:16,300 --> 00:51:18,460
but you're not saying anything.

710
00:51:22,380 --> 00:51:24,660
I'm afraid I must remain
neutral in all of this.

711
00:51:24,660 --> 00:51:25,980
Now, if you'll excuse me.

712
00:51:27,580 --> 00:51:30,260
<i>If someone were to tell me
that there exist among us</i>

713
00:51:30,260 --> 00:51:34,900
<i>authentic magicians, saints,
bodhisattvas,</i>

714
00:51:34,900 --> 00:51:37,980
<i>or anyone endowed
with miraculous powers,</i>

715
00:51:37,980 --> 00:51:39,380
<i>I would believe them.</i>

716
00:51:39,380 --> 00:51:43,100
In a certain sense,
what you say is true.

717
00:51:43,100 --> 00:51:45,060
But you've attained
the freedom to accept

718
00:51:45,060 --> 00:51:46,460
or reject
these new conditions

719
00:51:46,460 --> 00:51:51,100
to use them to finish
your life's work, or not.

720
00:51:51,100 --> 00:51:53,180
Have you decided?

721
00:51:55,060 --> 00:51:57,860
To use them for good

722
00:51:57,860 --> 00:51:59,380
or for evil.

723
00:51:59,380 --> 00:52:01,740
<i>Have you decided?</i>

724
00:52:17,180 --> 00:52:19,460
[PLAYING CLASSICAL MUSIC]

725
00:52:19,460 --> 00:52:21,340
[CHATTERING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

726
00:52:21,340 --> 00:52:22,700
<i>Despite my precautions,</i>

727
00:52:22,700 --> 00:52:24,420
<i>I was afraid
I would inadvertently</i>

728
00:52:24,420 --> 00:52:27,140
<i>give myself away
conversing with professors</i>

729
00:52:27,140 --> 00:52:29,220
<i>and colleagues
at the university.</i>

730
00:52:29,220 --> 00:52:32,380
<i>I knew more than any of them
and understood things</i>

731
00:52:32,380 --> 00:52:34,460
<i>they never even
suspected existed.</i>

732
00:52:50,100 --> 00:52:51,420
I know you're
a good friend

733
00:52:51,420 --> 00:52:53,260
of the Romanian
Professor Stanciulescu.

734
00:52:53,260 --> 00:52:57,700
I'm very sorry. I heard he died
in a plane crash, an accident.

735
00:52:57,700 --> 00:53:01,500
But we can talk about this
when my friend gets here.

736
00:53:01,500 --> 00:53:03,380
I told him to come at 9:00.

737
00:53:03,380 --> 00:53:05,220
Your friend?

738
00:53:05,220 --> 00:53:07,580
Dr. Monroe.

739
00:53:07,580 --> 00:53:10,580
The director of an important
gerontology foundation.

740
00:53:12,340 --> 00:53:15,860
He's Swiss, like me.

741
00:53:18,660 --> 00:53:20,140
[WHISPERING]
Like you.

742
00:53:26,580 --> 00:53:28,260
You know,
I do have a name.

743
00:53:29,420 --> 00:53:31,700
Would you like to know it?

744
00:53:42,460 --> 00:53:43,380
Be careful.

745
00:53:46,740 --> 00:53:48,620
He knows who you are.

746
00:53:48,620 --> 00:53:52,100
Hello, I'm Dr. Monroe.

747
00:53:52,100 --> 00:53:53,700
Head of the foundation
investigating

748
00:53:53,700 --> 00:53:55,140
the materials
of Professor Stanciulescu.

749
00:53:58,660 --> 00:54:01,260
I'm afraid I have no idea
to what you're referring.

750
00:54:01,260 --> 00:54:03,540
The belief that youth and life

751
00:54:03,540 --> 00:54:05,620
can be prolonged in any way
other than by the purely

752
00:54:05,620 --> 00:54:06,900
biochemical ones.

753
00:54:06,900 --> 00:54:07,820
You do know
what I'm referring to?

754
00:54:09,780 --> 00:54:11,060
No, I'm sorry.

755
00:54:11,060 --> 00:54:13,980
Methods proposed
by that Nazi, Dr. Rudolf.

756
00:54:13,980 --> 00:54:19,100
Electrocution by means
of a million or more volts.

757
00:54:19,100 --> 00:54:20,580
Insane.

758
00:54:20,580 --> 00:54:23,700
Fortunately, I believe
that method was never tried.

759
00:54:23,700 --> 00:54:26,460
But our informants said
that Professor Stanciulescu

760
00:54:26,460 --> 00:54:29,660
had worked with a somewhat
analogous case of rejuvenation

761
00:54:29,660 --> 00:54:31,500
induced by a bolt
of lightning.

762
00:54:34,820 --> 00:54:37,420
We know who you are,
Mr. Dominic Matei.

763
00:54:39,180 --> 00:54:41,940
Now, I have a prior engagement,
I really must run.

764
00:54:41,940 --> 00:54:43,980
I'm terribly sorry.
- I know.

765
00:54:43,980 --> 00:54:46,860
Perhaps we could have dinner.
Later tonight?

766
00:54:46,860 --> 00:54:48,500
[#]

767
00:55:07,140 --> 00:55:09,660
MONROE:
Mr. Matei?

768
00:55:09,660 --> 00:55:11,660
What do we do with time?

769
00:55:15,740 --> 00:55:17,940
That question,
"what do we do with time"

770
00:55:17,940 --> 00:55:23,380
expresses the supreme ambiguity
of the human condition.

771
00:55:23,380 --> 00:55:26,100
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

772
00:55:26,100 --> 00:55:28,940
An opportunity has been
given to us.

773
00:55:30,780 --> 00:55:32,700
We, the human race.

774
00:55:34,340 --> 00:55:35,500
"We"?

775
00:55:37,500 --> 00:55:38,260
No.

776
00:55:48,660 --> 00:55:51,620
You and I both know
what is coming:

777
00:55:51,620 --> 00:55:54,260
atomic warfare,
cataclysmic destruction.

778
00:55:54,260 --> 00:55:56,380
But unlike the others,

779
00:55:56,380 --> 00:56:00,660
I'm trying to find a meaning
to this impending catastrophe.

780
00:56:00,660 --> 00:56:02,780
Think of me as the last
European optimist.

781
00:56:02,780 --> 00:56:05,260
This can be our life's work.

782
00:56:05,260 --> 00:56:06,700
Please.

783
00:56:10,180 --> 00:56:13,900
There are a few of us who since
1938 have known that you exist.

784
00:56:15,900 --> 00:56:17,940
The fact that you appeared
all of a sudden

785
00:56:17,940 --> 00:56:20,060
means that you have
a special mission

786
00:56:20,060 --> 00:56:23,220
and that you possess means
of knowledge much superior

787
00:56:23,220 --> 00:56:25,020
to those available to us.

788
00:56:25,020 --> 00:56:26,340
You are gravely mistaken.

789
00:56:29,180 --> 00:56:33,180
What is indispensable
to a truly human existence?

790
00:56:33,180 --> 00:56:34,980
For instance,

791
00:56:34,980 --> 00:56:40,500
the Occidental artistic
treasury, music and poetry,

792
00:56:40,500 --> 00:56:43,620
but also a part
of classic philosophy,

793
00:56:43,620 --> 00:56:48,300
and above all, science.

794
00:56:48,300 --> 00:56:50,220
Post-historic man
will be allergic to science

795
00:56:50,220 --> 00:56:51,740
for at least
one or two centuries.

796
00:56:51,740 --> 00:56:55,820
No, always science.

797
00:56:55,820 --> 00:56:58,420
Science above all.
WOMAN: Dominic.

798
00:56:58,420 --> 00:56:59,900
I'm surprised at you.

799
00:56:59,900 --> 00:57:02,180
Dominic, don't believe
anything he says.

800
00:57:02,180 --> 00:57:03,140
[IN GERMAN]
Shut up!

801
00:57:03,140 --> 00:57:05,180
I will tell him the truth.

802
00:57:05,180 --> 00:57:07,420
[IN ENGLISH] Come, Dominic,
join me in this work.

803
00:57:07,420 --> 00:57:09,180
He is Dr. Josef Rudolf,

804
00:57:09,180 --> 00:57:11,060
Hitler's most
dedicated scientist.

805
00:57:13,340 --> 00:57:14,820
Adolf Hitler?

806
00:57:18,540 --> 00:57:20,540
If you actually knew him...

807
00:57:22,300 --> 00:57:24,900
If you had ever been with him,
in his presence...

808
00:57:26,580 --> 00:57:28,220
If I could describe it to you...

809
00:57:30,140 --> 00:57:32,340
Well, uh,

810
00:57:32,340 --> 00:57:33,620
you will meet him soon enough.

811
00:57:39,740 --> 00:57:41,740
No! The Gestapo
had Stanciulescu killed

812
00:57:41,740 --> 00:57:42,940
and Rudolf was the one--
Traitor!

813
00:57:44,220 --> 00:57:45,540
[RUDOLF SPEAKS IN GERMAN]

814
00:57:45,540 --> 00:57:47,420
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

815
00:57:47,420 --> 00:57:49,820
You have no choice
in the matter.

816
00:57:49,820 --> 00:57:51,300
WOMAN:
Dominic.

817
00:57:51,300 --> 00:57:56,380
[IN GERMAN] You were
the honey in my dreams.

818
00:57:56,380 --> 00:57:58,940
WOMAN [IN ENGLISH]:
Forgive me. Please, forgive me.

819
00:57:58,940 --> 00:57:59,900
[WOMAN SPEAKS IN GERMAN]

820
00:58:02,700 --> 00:58:05,180
It's true what he says.

821
00:58:06,740 --> 00:58:08,460
You really have no choice
in the matter.

822
00:58:13,540 --> 00:58:14,780
[PANTING]

823
00:58:29,540 --> 00:58:31,500
[RUDOLF GRUNTING]

824
00:58:46,780 --> 00:58:47,580
[RUDOLF YELLS]

825
00:58:47,580 --> 00:58:49,460
[GUNSHOT]

826
00:58:49,460 --> 00:58:50,540
[BODY COLLAPSES]

827
00:58:56,340 --> 00:58:59,020
[#]

828
00:58:59,020 --> 00:59:00,340
<i>[GUNSHOT]</i>

829
00:59:01,300 --> 00:59:02,140
<i>[GUNSHOT]</i>

830
00:59:03,500 --> 00:59:04,140
<i>[GUNSHOT]</i>

831
00:59:06,500 --> 00:59:07,580
<i>[BOMB WHISTLING]</i>

832
00:59:07,580 --> 00:59:10,060
<i>[GUNSHOTS]</i>

833
00:59:10,060 --> 00:59:11,020
<i>[BOMB WHISTLING]</i>

834
00:59:11,020 --> 00:59:13,060
<i>[GUNSHOTS]</i>

835
00:59:15,580 --> 00:59:16,580
<i>[BOMB WHISTLING]</i>

836
00:59:20,180 --> 00:59:24,460
DOMINIC:
Geneva 1955, 20th of August,

837
00:59:24,460 --> 00:59:26,860
about 10:31 a.m.
Dominic Matei.

838
00:59:26,860 --> 00:59:30,620
<i>I've decided to stop
making notes in English</i>

839
00:59:30,620 --> 00:59:32,660
<i>and instead to use
an artificial language</i>

840
00:59:32,660 --> 00:59:34,300
<i>of my own invention.</i>

841
00:59:34,300 --> 00:59:38,780
[IN NEW LANGUAGE] Now I can
describe paradoxical situations

842
00:59:38,780 --> 00:59:42,300
impossible to express
in any existing language.

843
00:59:42,300 --> 00:59:44,500
This will permit me
to reveal facts

844
00:59:44,500 --> 00:59:47,780
I have not dared
to confess in writing.

845
00:59:47,780 --> 00:59:50,180
This language will
only be deciphered

846
00:59:50,180 --> 00:59:53,340
by means
of a perfected computer.

847
00:59:53,340 --> 00:59:56,620
So my testimony is addressed
to the future,

848
00:59:56,620 --> 00:59:59,500
let us say in the year 2010.

849
00:59:59,500 --> 01:00:01,220
But to whom?

850
01:00:01,220 --> 01:00:03,700
The coming nuclear wars

851
01:00:03,700 --> 01:00:06,300
will destroy many civilizations.

852
01:00:06,300 --> 01:00:09,380
Undoubtedly, this will unleash

853
01:00:09,380 --> 01:00:14,980
a wave of deep pessimism,
historically unprecedented.

854
01:00:14,980 --> 01:00:17,660
A general despondency.

855
01:00:17,660 --> 01:00:20,860
My testimony,
deciphered in the future,

856
01:00:20,860 --> 01:00:23,580
could counter the despair

857
01:00:23,580 --> 01:00:26,300
because it shows
the potential of humanity:

858
01:00:26,300 --> 01:00:28,140
<i>a species superior
to Homo sapiens,</i>

859
01:00:28,140 --> 01:00:31,620
<i>born in a far-off future.</i>

860
01:00:31,620 --> 01:00:34,300
<i>This depends
on the preservation</i>

861
01:00:34,300 --> 01:00:37,580
<i>of the material
in the safe-deposit box.</i>

862
01:00:37,580 --> 01:00:41,180
<i>I don't know how
this will be assured.</i>

863
01:00:41,180 --> 01:00:43,140
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

864
01:00:45,060 --> 01:00:48,100
<i>[ON TAPE] But I do not
doubt that the material</i>

865
01:00:48,100 --> 01:00:51,340
<i>will be preserved.</i>

866
01:00:53,180 --> 01:00:56,540
<i>Otherwise,</i>

867
01:00:56,540 --> 01:00:58,060
<i>my life would have
no meaning.</i>

868
01:01:04,020 --> 01:01:04,780
[HORN HONKING]

869
01:01:08,860 --> 01:01:09,980
WOMAN [IN ENGLISH]:
Hello!

870
01:01:09,980 --> 01:01:12,060
[HORN HONKING]

871
01:01:12,060 --> 01:01:13,620
Excuse me,

872
01:01:13,620 --> 01:01:15,580
what's the best way
up to the top?

873
01:01:15,580 --> 01:01:17,100
[#]

874
01:01:23,900 --> 01:01:25,260
Is it Laura?

875
01:01:25,260 --> 01:01:27,780
She's afraid of curvy roads.

876
01:01:27,780 --> 01:01:29,860
I really don't think
you should go on.

877
01:01:29,860 --> 01:01:31,420
There's a storm coming in.

878
01:01:31,420 --> 01:01:36,300
We're used to mountain storms.
And anyway, we can't wait.

879
01:01:36,300 --> 01:01:37,660
It is.

880
01:01:41,940 --> 01:01:44,260
Our vacation will
be over in a few days.

881
01:01:44,260 --> 01:01:45,220
Maybe I can help.

882
01:01:49,260 --> 01:01:50,340
That's it.

883
01:01:52,420 --> 01:01:53,700
That's it.

884
01:01:55,100 --> 01:01:58,620
I'm Veronica.
What's your name?

885
01:01:58,620 --> 01:01:59,700
Dominic.

886
01:01:59,700 --> 01:02:01,900
With her,
you use your real name.

887
01:02:05,340 --> 01:02:05,900
VERONICA:
Thank you.

888
01:02:13,260 --> 01:02:14,620
Be careful.

889
01:02:14,620 --> 01:02:16,020
VERONICA:
Goodbye, Dominic.

890
01:02:18,860 --> 01:02:21,020
<i>DOMINIC:
I can only guess what happened.</i>

891
01:02:21,020 --> 01:02:22,860
<i>When the big storm broke out,</i>

892
01:02:22,860 --> 01:02:24,100
they were probably
on the road

893
01:02:24,100 --> 01:02:25,660
that runs under
the mountain wall,

894
01:02:25,660 --> 01:02:27,780
where most
of the lightning struck.

895
01:02:27,780 --> 01:02:30,140
I'm afraid they could have
been buried in a rockslide

896
01:02:30,140 --> 01:02:33,060
or a close strike of lightning
can cause a heart attack.

897
01:02:35,900 --> 01:02:36,860
Your name?

898
01:02:36,860 --> 01:02:39,020
Martin Audricourt.

899
01:02:42,100 --> 01:02:42,580
Passport, please.

900
01:02:49,820 --> 01:02:52,860
You know, I can always
go in a taxi by myself.

901
01:02:54,660 --> 01:02:57,140
If I need help, I'll call
from the first service station.

902
01:03:07,900 --> 01:03:10,940
DOMINIC: I don't think they could
have had time to reach the shelter.

903
01:03:10,940 --> 01:03:13,020
They could have taken refuge

904
01:03:13,020 --> 01:03:15,260
in one of the crevices
in the wall.

905
01:03:17,540 --> 01:03:19,060
Oh, there's their car.

906
01:03:22,300 --> 01:03:23,780
There's a woman
over here.

907
01:03:37,660 --> 01:03:39,020
She's dead.

908
01:03:48,060 --> 01:03:51,940
<i>VERONICA:
Om, shanti</i>

909
01:03:51,940 --> 01:03:54,140
<i>Shanti</i>

910
01:03:54,140 --> 01:03:55,420
[GASPS]

911
01:03:55,420 --> 01:03:56,700
Veronica?

912
01:03:56,700 --> 01:03:57,660
[WHIMPERING]

913
01:03:57,660 --> 01:04:00,460
What happened?
Are you all right?

914
01:04:02,500 --> 01:04:05,180
[CHANTING IN SANSKRIT]

915
01:04:05,180 --> 01:04:05,740
Sanskrit.

916
01:04:08,420 --> 01:04:09,820
How can it be?

917
01:04:13,500 --> 01:04:15,340
[CHANTING IN SANSKRIT]

918
01:04:32,380 --> 01:04:34,980
[#]

919
01:04:38,940 --> 01:04:40,180
[VERONICA YELLING]

920
01:04:40,180 --> 01:04:42,300
[DOMINIC SPEAKING
IN SANSKRIT]

921
01:04:45,020 --> 01:04:47,900
She's had a shock.
She's suffering from amnesia.

922
01:04:47,900 --> 01:04:50,260
What language is that?
What is she speaking?

923
01:04:50,260 --> 01:04:53,820
It's an Indian language,
I think.

924
01:04:53,820 --> 01:04:59,580
Her papers identify her
as Veronica Buehler, age 25.

925
01:04:59,580 --> 01:05:01,100
Occupation: school teacher.

926
01:05:01,100 --> 01:05:03,740
Living in Liestal,
Canton Bâle-Campagne.

927
01:05:03,740 --> 01:05:05,500
Excuse me.
- Please.

928
01:05:05,500 --> 01:05:07,900
You're the only one
who can calm her

929
01:05:07,900 --> 01:05:10,660
and speak her language,
Mr...?

930
01:05:10,660 --> 01:05:11,980
Audricourt.

931
01:05:11,980 --> 01:05:13,420
I'm a student of linguistics.

932
01:05:30,860 --> 01:05:33,180
[IN SANSKRIT]
Greetings.

933
01:05:33,180 --> 01:05:35,580
Greetings.

934
01:05:36,700 --> 01:05:38,900
What is your name?

935
01:05:43,380 --> 01:05:47,460
It is a pleasure
to make your acquaintance.

936
01:05:50,500 --> 01:05:53,060
My name is Rupini.

937
01:05:56,220 --> 01:05:57,220
[IN ENGLISH]
Thank you.

938
01:06:02,820 --> 01:06:04,220
Good morning.

939
01:06:07,380 --> 01:06:09,500
What can you tell us,
Mr. Audricourt?

940
01:06:21,660 --> 01:06:23,740
The young woman believes

941
01:06:23,740 --> 01:06:25,980
she is living
in northeastern India

942
01:06:25,980 --> 01:06:26,900
14 centuries ago.

943
01:06:28,900 --> 01:06:30,380
She feels
that she has spent

944
01:06:30,380 --> 01:06:34,580
several months
in a cave meditating.

945
01:06:36,420 --> 01:06:38,940
Now, this is where she was
when a big storm broke out

946
01:06:38,940 --> 01:06:42,700
and she saw lightning strike
above her on the mountain.

947
01:06:42,700 --> 01:06:47,580
Many large rocks were dislodged,
blocking the mouth of the cave.

948
01:06:50,340 --> 01:06:51,420
Is that all?

949
01:06:51,420 --> 01:06:54,260
She asserts her name
is Rupini,

950
01:06:56,060 --> 01:06:58,620
daughter of Nagabhatta,

951
01:06:58,620 --> 01:07:02,420
descended from one of the first
families to convert to Buddhism.

952
01:07:04,220 --> 01:07:10,220
She became a disciple
of the philosopher Chandrakirti,

953
01:07:10,220 --> 01:07:15,020
which is why she was in the cave
copying down his works.

954
01:07:15,020 --> 01:07:16,500
I see.

955
01:07:18,500 --> 01:07:21,380
Would you mind if I discuss this
a moment with my colleagues?

956
01:07:23,260 --> 01:07:23,780
Not at all.

957
01:07:29,660 --> 01:07:31,540
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

958
01:07:38,540 --> 01:07:39,140
[COUGHS]

959
01:07:41,980 --> 01:07:44,660
We will invite
some doctors from, uh,

960
01:07:44,660 --> 01:07:47,500
Zurich, Basel and Geneva
to come to see her.

961
01:07:48,940 --> 01:07:50,300
I...

962
01:07:50,300 --> 01:07:52,540
If I might make a suggestion?

963
01:07:52,540 --> 01:07:54,140
Yes.

964
01:07:54,140 --> 01:07:57,020
Perhaps some experts from
the Oriental Institute in Rome

965
01:07:57,020 --> 01:07:58,460
might be necessary.

966
01:07:58,460 --> 01:08:01,700
Necessary for what?

967
01:08:01,700 --> 01:08:05,340
Well, to confirm
if what she's saying is fact.

968
01:08:06,460 --> 01:08:08,020
Fact?

969
01:08:08,020 --> 01:08:09,060
Exactly.

970
01:08:15,500 --> 01:08:17,780
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

971
01:08:17,780 --> 01:08:20,060
[IN ITALIAN] I present to
you Professor Giuseppe Tucci

972
01:08:20,060 --> 01:08:21,620
from the Oriental Institute
in Rome.

973
01:08:21,620 --> 01:08:23,380
I am Blasi, his assistant.

974
01:08:23,380 --> 01:08:26,140
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

975
01:08:26,140 --> 01:08:28,500
[IN ENGLISH] Professor
Tucci, it's an honor.

976
01:08:36,660 --> 01:08:40,060
Before we begin,
who wrote the telegram

977
01:08:40,060 --> 01:08:41,820
that included
some of the particulars?

978
01:08:41,820 --> 01:08:43,900
I did, professor.

979
01:08:43,900 --> 01:08:45,340
You're a Sanskritist?

980
01:08:45,340 --> 01:08:47,900
Not exactly. Excuse me.

981
01:08:47,900 --> 01:08:50,140
Uh, but I have an interest
in Oriental studies.

982
01:08:50,140 --> 01:08:52,820
I came only because
of your report.

983
01:08:52,820 --> 01:08:54,140
Thank you.

984
01:08:54,140 --> 01:08:56,460
[IN ITALIAN]
You did well.

985
01:09:03,460 --> 01:09:05,540
[IN SANSKRIT]
Well-being, your ladyship.

986
01:09:05,540 --> 01:09:06,660
Well-being, your ladyship.

987
01:09:08,900 --> 01:09:11,180
Welcome to both of you.

988
01:09:13,540 --> 01:09:16,020
Where am I?

989
01:09:16,020 --> 01:09:19,820
Why doesn't anybody
understand me?

990
01:09:22,260 --> 01:09:29,700
As in dreams, the mind presents
the appearance of duality.

991
01:09:29,700 --> 01:09:32,580
[IN ENGLISH] We've had some of her
remarks translated into English.

992
01:09:34,460 --> 01:09:38,620
The young woman's knowledge
of Madhyamika philosophy

993
01:09:38,620 --> 01:09:41,940
and her master, Chandrakirti,
is convincing.

994
01:09:43,380 --> 01:09:45,740
The discussion only became
delicate whenever Rupini

995
01:09:45,740 --> 01:09:51,100
asked what had happened to her,
where she was

996
01:09:51,100 --> 01:09:53,060
and why no one understood her.

997
01:09:53,060 --> 01:09:54,940
What did you tell her,
professor?

998
01:09:54,940 --> 01:09:57,020
[IN ITALIAN] I always
begin by reminding of maya.

999
01:09:57,020 --> 01:09:59,100
[CHUCKLES]
The cosmic illusion.

1000
01:09:59,100 --> 01:10:01,500
TUCCI:
The great witch.

1001
01:10:01,500 --> 01:10:03,620
[IN ENGLISH] Actually it's
not a dream, I told her,

1002
01:10:03,620 --> 01:10:04,740
but it takes part

1003
01:10:04,740 --> 01:10:07,220
in the illusory nature
of dreaming,

1004
01:10:07,220 --> 01:10:12,260
because it is the future,
therefore, of time.

1005
01:10:12,260 --> 01:10:16,060
Now, time is
par excellence unreal.

1006
01:10:16,060 --> 01:10:18,180
I don't believe
I convinced her.

1007
01:10:18,180 --> 01:10:19,340
But fortunately, she's, uh,

1008
01:10:19,340 --> 01:10:21,180
enthusiastic about logic
and dialectics,

1009
01:10:21,180 --> 01:10:23,100
and that's mainly
what we discussed.

1010
01:10:23,100 --> 01:10:24,500
MAN [IN ITALIAN]:
Uh, professor,

1011
01:10:24,500 --> 01:10:28,140
could all this possibly be...?

1012
01:10:28,140 --> 01:10:30,620
How shall I say?

1013
01:10:30,620 --> 01:10:32,060
[IN ENGLISH]
Fact?

1014
01:10:32,060 --> 01:10:34,060
"Fact"?

1015
01:10:36,220 --> 01:10:37,660
Mmm.

1016
01:10:37,660 --> 01:10:39,460
I would suggest
a journey to India,

1017
01:10:39,460 --> 01:10:42,100
more precisely to the province
of Uttar Pradesh,

1018
01:10:42,100 --> 01:10:46,100
to the caves where Rupini
claims to have meditated.

1019
01:10:46,100 --> 01:10:49,300
I should think
the Oriental Institute of Rome,

1020
01:10:49,300 --> 01:10:52,980
of which I am president,
would sponsor the expedition.

1021
01:10:52,980 --> 01:10:54,020
And, young man,

1022
01:10:54,020 --> 01:10:56,700
I think you should
accompany us to India.

1023
01:10:56,700 --> 01:10:58,380
I'd be delighted,
professor.

1024
01:10:58,380 --> 01:10:59,900
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

1025
01:10:59,900 --> 01:11:02,420
It's been understood she will
be put into a deep sleep

1026
01:11:02,420 --> 01:11:03,660
before leaving the clinic

1027
01:11:03,660 --> 01:11:05,180
and will continue
to sleep

1028
01:11:05,180 --> 01:11:07,980
until we reach the vicinity
of the caves.

1029
01:11:09,020 --> 01:11:10,860
[#]

1030
01:11:23,860 --> 01:11:24,900
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

1031
01:11:38,300 --> 01:11:39,340
[TIRES SCREECH]

1032
01:11:49,340 --> 01:11:50,780
[CHATTERING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1033
01:11:50,780 --> 01:11:52,300
MAN:
Start rolling. Rolling!

1034
01:11:52,300 --> 01:11:53,540
Tucci! Tucci, look here!

1035
01:11:53,540 --> 01:11:54,580
[MAN SPEAKS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1036
01:12:14,180 --> 01:12:15,620
[#]

1037
01:12:30,180 --> 01:12:32,420
We are very close
to the frontier of Nepal.

1038
01:12:32,420 --> 01:12:34,620
According to Rupini's account,

1039
01:12:34,620 --> 01:12:36,980
this is where we'll find the
cave where she would meditate.

1040
01:12:47,780 --> 01:12:50,540
[CAMERA WHIRRING]

1041
01:12:53,660 --> 01:12:55,700
[GOATS BLEATING]

1042
01:13:00,700 --> 01:13:03,340
We are very fortunate in having
a pandit from Gorakhpur

1043
01:13:03,340 --> 01:13:05,620
familiar with
the Madhyamika philosophy.

1044
01:13:05,620 --> 01:13:07,420
He'll be at her side
when she awakens.

1045
01:13:07,420 --> 01:13:10,260
[CAMERA WHIRRING]

1046
01:13:14,340 --> 01:13:15,980
[SPEAKING IN SANSKRIT]

1047
01:13:18,940 --> 01:13:20,460
Everyone,
hide themselves.

1048
01:13:20,460 --> 01:13:21,740
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

1049
01:13:23,140 --> 01:13:24,220
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

1050
01:13:24,220 --> 01:13:26,860
[CAMERA WHIRRING]

1051
01:13:36,620 --> 01:13:38,900
[IN SANSKRIT]
No form,

1052
01:13:38,900 --> 01:13:41,420
no feeling,

1053
01:13:41,420 --> 01:13:42,620
no thought,

1054
01:13:42,620 --> 01:13:45,100
no choice,

1055
01:13:46,740 --> 01:13:48,460
no consciousness.

1056
01:13:53,180 --> 01:13:55,580
Gone, gone,

1057
01:13:55,580 --> 01:13:58,180
gone beyond,
completely gone.

1058
01:13:59,420 --> 01:14:01,380
Enlightenment.

1059
01:14:01,380 --> 01:14:02,660
So be it.

1060
01:14:03,660 --> 01:14:04,660
Welcome.

1061
01:14:15,500 --> 01:14:19,100
Why did it take you so long?

1062
01:14:19,100 --> 01:14:21,500
I was already here.

1063
01:14:29,140 --> 01:14:30,980
[BELLS JINGLING]
[GOATS BLEATING]

1064
01:14:43,340 --> 01:14:44,780
[#]

1065
01:14:47,100 --> 01:14:50,940
I know this place.

1066
01:15:10,780 --> 01:15:12,700
[IN ENGLISH]
Stay back. Hide yourself.

1067
01:15:19,980 --> 01:15:21,380
[IN SANSKRIT]
Over here!

1068
01:15:40,660 --> 01:15:41,940
Ah!

1069
01:15:41,940 --> 01:15:43,940
[YELLS]

1070
01:15:43,940 --> 01:15:45,420
[IN ENGLISH]
Oh, God.

1071
01:15:45,420 --> 01:15:46,420
Are you all right?

1072
01:15:56,180 --> 01:15:57,940
DOMINIC:
Just be still. Lay still.

1073
01:15:59,220 --> 01:16:00,540
Just rest.

1074
01:16:00,540 --> 01:16:01,820
Veronica.

1075
01:16:03,380 --> 01:16:05,220
TUCCI [IN ITALIAN]:
She recognized it.

1076
01:16:05,220 --> 01:16:07,580
This is the cave!

1077
01:16:07,580 --> 01:16:09,020
But the entrance is blocked.

1078
01:16:09,020 --> 01:16:10,660
[CAMERA WHIRRING]

1079
01:16:27,980 --> 01:16:29,660
[#]

1080
01:16:35,420 --> 01:16:37,380
[SPEAKING IN SANSKRIT]

1081
01:17:24,700 --> 01:17:28,540
[IN ENGLISH] I don't think
you'll be needing me for a while.

1082
01:17:38,980 --> 01:17:40,380
[CROWD CHATTERING]

1083
01:17:43,940 --> 01:17:44,900
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

1084
01:17:51,940 --> 01:17:53,620
WOMAN:
She is awake,

1085
01:17:53,620 --> 01:17:55,740
but she has not
opened her eyes.

1086
01:18:03,220 --> 01:18:04,780
[IN SANSKRIT]
Greetings.

1087
01:18:09,140 --> 01:18:12,460
How are you feeling, Rupini?

1088
01:18:18,980 --> 01:18:22,940
[IN ENGLISH] Didn't we--? Didn't
we ask directions of you today?

1089
01:18:25,740 --> 01:18:27,580
<i>My name is Veronica Buehler,</i>

1090
01:18:27,580 --> 01:18:30,140
<i>and I speak three languages:</i>

1091
01:18:30,140 --> 01:18:32,620
<i>German, French and English.</i>

1092
01:18:32,620 --> 01:18:35,660
<i>TUCCI: Have you ever tried to
learn any Oriental language?</i>

1093
01:18:35,660 --> 01:18:36,780
<i>Never.</i>

1094
01:18:36,780 --> 01:18:39,140
<i>TUCCI:
Or have you ever read anything</i>

1095
01:18:39,140 --> 01:18:41,020
<i>about India
or Indian culture?</i>

1096
01:18:41,020 --> 01:18:42,780
<i>Some popular books.</i>

1097
01:18:42,780 --> 01:18:43,900
<i>TUCCI:
Like?</i>

1098
01:18:43,900 --> 01:18:46,700
<i>Heh. Rudyard Kipling,
I think?</i>

1099
01:18:46,700 --> 01:18:47,940
The Jungle Book.

1100
01:18:47,940 --> 01:18:49,460
<i>[CROWD LAUGHS]
Have you ever heard</i>

1101
01:18:49,460 --> 01:18:51,700
<i>the name Rupini?</i>

1102
01:18:51,700 --> 01:18:53,340
<i>No.</i>

1103
01:18:53,340 --> 01:18:55,300
<i>TUCCI:
In an earlier existence,</i>

1104
01:18:55,300 --> 01:18:57,860
<i>Veronica Buehler
had been Rupini.</i>

1105
01:18:57,860 --> 01:19:01,980
<i>I would say, for the vast
majority of the Orientalists,</i>

1106
01:19:01,980 --> 01:19:07,100
<i>a clear example of
the transmigration of the soul.</i>

1107
01:19:07,100 --> 01:19:09,180
<i>And, young man, your opinion?</i>

1108
01:19:09,180 --> 01:19:11,380
<i>As a neophyte Orientalist,</i>

1109
01:19:11,380 --> 01:19:13,660
<i>I can only cite some classical
Indian conceptions,</i>

1110
01:19:13,660 --> 01:19:16,820
<i>from Upanishads
to Gautama Buddha.</i>

1111
01:19:16,820 --> 01:19:19,700
<i>BLASI: Excuse me. It is
precisely in the Upanishads</i>

1112
01:19:19,700 --> 01:19:22,700
<i>in the Brhadaranyaka
and Chandogya Upanishads</i>

1113
01:19:22,700 --> 01:19:25,900
<i>that one can find this belief
for the first time.</i>

1114
01:19:25,900 --> 01:19:27,700
<i>This is karma, isn't it?</i>

1115
01:19:27,700 --> 01:19:29,580
VERONICA:
But it's hard for me to believe

1116
01:19:29,580 --> 01:19:31,140
that I ever existed before.

1117
01:19:31,140 --> 01:19:33,020
How did you say?

1118
01:19:33,020 --> 01:19:34,580
Metempsychosis.

1119
01:19:34,580 --> 01:19:36,940
Metempsychosis.
- Mm-hm.

1120
01:19:36,940 --> 01:19:38,820
That absolutely
doesn't make sense to me.

1121
01:19:41,020 --> 01:19:42,460
Maybe...

1122
01:19:42,460 --> 01:19:43,980
What?

1123
01:19:43,980 --> 01:19:46,780
Maybe I was possessed
by an evil spirit.

1124
01:19:46,780 --> 01:19:48,700
Well...

1125
01:19:48,700 --> 01:19:50,260
VERONICA:
They never leave us alone.

1126
01:19:50,260 --> 01:19:53,060
[CAMERA CLICKS]
It's all so confusing.

1127
01:19:53,060 --> 01:19:55,100
I'm afraid
I'm going crazy.

1128
01:19:55,100 --> 01:19:56,820
[CAMERA CLICKING]

1129
01:19:59,060 --> 01:20:00,460
[CROWD CHATTERING]

1130
01:20:05,140 --> 01:20:07,860
Hello, Miss Veronica,
just an interview.

1131
01:20:07,860 --> 01:20:10,140
That's enough. Let's go.

1132
01:20:10,140 --> 01:20:11,380
DOMINIC:
Taxi!

1133
01:20:15,980 --> 01:20:17,660
Just drive, drive anywhere.

1134
01:20:17,660 --> 01:20:18,860
[DOMINIC & VERONICA LAUGH]

1135
01:20:52,700 --> 01:20:56,020
I-- I think
we should get away. I...

1136
01:20:57,660 --> 01:21:00,460
I think we should go somewhere.
We should be alone.

1137
01:21:00,460 --> 01:21:02,180
We should go to, uh,
somewhere beautiful,

1138
01:21:02,180 --> 01:21:03,020
a Mediterranean island.

1139
01:21:05,180 --> 01:21:08,060
Dominic, that would make me
very, very happy.

1140
01:21:08,060 --> 01:21:09,900
[#]

1141
01:21:20,580 --> 01:21:22,460
[BIRDS CAWING]

1142
01:21:31,300 --> 01:21:32,740
[CRICKET CHIRPING]

1143
01:21:54,460 --> 01:21:56,660
[BIRD SQUAWKING]

1144
01:21:56,660 --> 01:21:59,220
VERONICA:
Look, that bird.

1145
01:21:59,220 --> 01:22:01,540
What kind of birds
do they have in Malta?

1146
01:22:01,540 --> 01:22:03,100
DOMINIC:
That's a Maltese falcon.

1147
01:22:03,100 --> 01:22:03,860
[VERONICA CHUCKLES]

1148
01:22:21,980 --> 01:22:23,620
[IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]
Welcome.

1149
01:22:23,620 --> 01:22:25,780
[IN ENGLISH]
Thank you.

1150
01:22:31,620 --> 01:22:33,300
No, that's fine.
Thank you.

1151
01:22:33,300 --> 01:22:34,620
Thank you.

1152
01:22:40,460 --> 01:22:41,900
Thanks very much.

1153
01:22:45,700 --> 01:22:47,420
Finally alone.

1154
01:22:53,020 --> 01:22:55,660
Dominic,
it's beautiful here.

1155
01:22:55,660 --> 01:22:57,020
Yes, it is.

1156
01:23:06,820 --> 01:23:09,620
When I first opened my eyes
and saw you...

1157
01:23:12,980 --> 01:23:16,060
I confess I was thinking,

1158
01:23:16,060 --> 01:23:20,540
if I were three
or four years older and...

1159
01:23:23,580 --> 01:23:25,340
if he were
to ask me to marry him...

1160
01:23:29,500 --> 01:23:31,100
I would say yes.

1161
01:23:32,060 --> 01:23:34,580
[#]

1162
01:23:42,460 --> 01:23:43,620
Veronica.

1163
01:23:58,740 --> 01:24:00,420
DOMINIC:
My love.

1164
01:24:00,420 --> 01:24:02,460
Is it true?

1165
01:24:11,260 --> 01:24:12,500
Yes.

1166
01:24:21,660 --> 01:24:23,420
I've always loved you.

1167
01:24:51,140 --> 01:24:51,780
Veronica?

1168
01:25:04,020 --> 01:25:06,220
[MUTTERS]

1169
01:25:06,220 --> 01:25:08,580
[CLEARS THROAT]

1170
01:25:08,580 --> 01:25:12,900
[SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1171
01:25:37,540 --> 01:25:38,540
Do you understand it?

1172
01:25:40,620 --> 01:25:42,660
I don't know this language.

1173
01:25:44,660 --> 01:25:48,300
Ancient... Beyond...

1174
01:25:48,300 --> 01:25:49,740
Why else did you have
to know her?

1175
01:25:54,620 --> 01:25:58,380
[CONTINUES
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1176
01:26:10,820 --> 01:26:12,700
[PANTING]

1177
01:26:14,260 --> 01:26:15,100
[GROANING]

1178
01:26:20,420 --> 01:26:21,820
[CLEARS THROAT]

1179
01:26:24,020 --> 01:26:25,020
[CLEARS THROAT]

1180
01:26:26,500 --> 01:26:30,580
[SCREAMS]

1181
01:26:33,060 --> 01:26:35,220
[#]

1182
01:26:37,900 --> 01:26:39,580
[PANTING]

1183
01:26:46,460 --> 01:26:47,620
Veronica?

1184
01:26:52,420 --> 01:26:53,380
Veronica...

1185
01:26:53,380 --> 01:26:53,860
[HISSING]

1186
01:27:01,020 --> 01:27:01,980
[GRUNTS]

1187
01:27:08,980 --> 01:27:10,060
It's all right.

1188
01:27:10,060 --> 01:27:12,060
That's all right.
It's all right.

1189
01:27:12,060 --> 01:27:14,620
I've got you.
I've got you.

1190
01:27:14,620 --> 01:27:16,820
I've got you, darling.
[SNIFFLES]

1191
01:27:16,820 --> 01:27:19,460
I've got you, Laura.

1192
01:27:19,460 --> 01:27:22,300
[WHIMPERS]
It's all right.

1193
01:27:22,300 --> 01:27:24,100
I've got you.

1194
01:27:24,100 --> 01:27:26,980
I've got you, darling.
I've got you, Laura.

1195
01:27:30,340 --> 01:27:32,660
I love you, darling.

1196
01:27:32,660 --> 01:27:34,180
I love you.

1197
01:27:43,260 --> 01:27:46,620
<i>[VERONICA SPEAKING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]</i>

1198
01:27:58,900 --> 01:28:01,860
[TAPE REWINDING]

1199
01:28:04,780 --> 01:28:07,700
<i>[VERONICA SPEAKING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]</i>

1200
01:28:23,740 --> 01:28:24,500
[TAPE CLICKS OFF]

1201
01:28:36,420 --> 01:28:38,140
Was that Rupini's voice?

1202
01:28:38,140 --> 01:28:40,380
Mm-hm. Yes.

1203
01:28:40,380 --> 01:28:42,460
She's moving back in time

1204
01:28:42,460 --> 01:28:46,020
from Sanskrit
to earlier languages.

1205
01:28:46,020 --> 01:28:47,380
That was Egyptian.

1206
01:28:53,340 --> 01:28:55,940
Perhaps you'll take us back
to a time before history.

1207
01:28:58,060 --> 01:29:00,100
The origins of language,

1208
01:29:00,100 --> 01:29:03,660
which is where I've always
wanted to go, but I never could.

1209
01:29:03,660 --> 01:29:06,140
But it's helping me
finish my work.

1210
01:29:06,140 --> 01:29:07,020
Good.

1211
01:29:08,620 --> 01:29:10,820
Good. I want to help you.

1212
01:29:10,820 --> 01:29:11,580
You know, I'm...

1213
01:29:13,900 --> 01:29:17,460
I'm 88 years old, really.

1214
01:29:17,460 --> 01:29:18,980
[#]

1215
01:29:18,980 --> 01:29:20,420
[CHUCKLES]

1216
01:29:22,700 --> 01:29:25,540
If I added up all the years
Rupini lived,

1217
01:29:25,540 --> 01:29:26,380
I'd be older than you.

1218
01:29:28,340 --> 01:29:29,060
Well, then let's go dancing.

1219
01:29:34,620 --> 01:29:36,060
[FIREWORKS POPPING]

1220
01:29:39,780 --> 01:29:41,020
[LAUGHTER]

1221
01:29:46,780 --> 01:29:48,820
[CROWD CHATTERING]

1222
01:29:48,820 --> 01:29:50,660
[BAND PLAYING MELLOW MUSIC]

1223
01:29:59,820 --> 01:30:00,780
DOMINIC:
Thank you.

1224
01:30:14,660 --> 01:30:16,140
[LAUGHING]

1225
01:30:19,420 --> 01:30:20,860
I don't think
we'll be recognized,

1226
01:30:20,860 --> 01:30:23,260
even with our pictures
in all those magazines.

1227
01:30:23,260 --> 01:30:27,180
Well, our pictures
are still appearing.

1228
01:30:27,180 --> 01:30:28,260
Let me see.

1229
01:30:41,380 --> 01:30:43,100
[#]

1230
01:30:46,580 --> 01:30:47,500
What's the matter?

1231
01:30:55,100 --> 01:30:57,900
I feel tired all the time,

1232
01:30:57,900 --> 01:31:00,900
and I don't understand why.

1233
01:31:00,900 --> 01:31:05,460
Something is happening
inside me. I can feel it.

1234
01:31:05,460 --> 01:31:06,940
THE DOUBLE:
And she's right.

1235
01:31:06,940 --> 01:31:09,780
The paramediumistic ecstasies
have exhausted her.

1236
01:31:13,180 --> 01:31:15,700
[CORK POPS]

1237
01:31:15,700 --> 01:31:17,140
MAN:
Champagne?

1238
01:31:22,860 --> 01:31:24,140
[MAN SPEAKS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1239
01:31:57,340 --> 01:31:59,220
[#]

1240
01:32:05,380 --> 01:32:06,980
[CLOCK TICKING]

1241
01:32:50,860 --> 01:32:52,140
Veronica?

1242
01:33:00,100 --> 01:33:01,660
Veronica!

1243
01:33:12,300 --> 01:33:14,220
[SHOUTS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1244
01:33:21,100 --> 01:33:24,380
No! Veronica, don't!

1245
01:33:26,300 --> 01:33:27,700
Veronica!

1246
01:33:28,860 --> 01:33:29,540
I was so worried!

1247
01:33:31,540 --> 01:33:32,900
What is it?

1248
01:33:32,900 --> 01:33:34,700
It was a dream.

1249
01:33:34,700 --> 01:33:37,660
A bad dream.

1250
01:33:37,660 --> 01:33:40,020
What was--? What was it?

1251
01:33:42,460 --> 01:33:45,620
I was somewhere beside a river,
and someone,

1252
01:33:45,620 --> 01:33:47,820
a stranger with a head
like a dog,

1253
01:33:47,820 --> 01:33:49,420
was coming toward me.

1254
01:33:49,420 --> 01:33:52,060
And in his hand, he--
He had...

1255
01:33:54,460 --> 01:33:56,100
Explain it to me!

1256
01:33:56,100 --> 01:33:58,780
I want to know
what Rupini knows.

1257
01:33:58,780 --> 01:34:02,300
She knows things
that we don't understand yet.

1258
01:34:02,300 --> 01:34:04,180
No. Let me--

1259
01:34:04,180 --> 01:34:06,300
No, no!

1260
01:34:06,300 --> 01:34:07,620
Don't ever leave me.

1261
01:34:07,620 --> 01:34:08,860
I'll never leave you.

1262
01:34:08,860 --> 01:34:10,900
Don't ever leave me.
I'll never leave you.

1263
01:34:10,900 --> 01:34:13,260
Don't ever leave me.

1264
01:34:13,260 --> 01:34:14,300
I'll never leave you.

1265
01:34:21,660 --> 01:34:22,940
[MOANING SOFTLY]

1266
01:34:35,260 --> 01:34:37,100
[#]

1267
01:34:46,940 --> 01:34:48,780
[GROWLING]

1268
01:34:58,460 --> 01:35:00,140
Veronica.
[MOANS]

1269
01:35:07,980 --> 01:35:11,660
The stranger in your dream
was probably Shiva.

1270
01:35:14,460 --> 01:35:16,900
And in his hand, a skull.

1271
01:35:18,940 --> 01:35:23,460
For Shiva is both creator
and destroyer combined.

1272
01:35:30,340 --> 01:35:31,780
[#]

1273
01:36:04,620 --> 01:36:05,580
[SIGHS]

1274
01:36:16,100 --> 01:36:17,060
Dominic?

1275
01:36:17,060 --> 01:36:18,500
There's someone
who looks like you

1276
01:36:18,500 --> 01:36:20,540
spying on us.

1277
01:36:20,540 --> 01:36:21,780
I didn't notice anyone.

1278
01:36:21,780 --> 01:36:23,420
By the gate.

1279
01:36:23,420 --> 01:36:24,420
Come and look.

